<content>1 Welcome to your wiki


Welcome to your [second generation wiki&gt;http://www.xwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/Main/SecondGenerationWiki]! 
It is an online, shared workspace that will allow you to collaborate effectively with others. You can use it for many purposes:

* Project Management
* Collaborative Writing
* Efficient Document Sharing

... the only limit is your imagination!

1.1 How to start

Maybe you are used to work with a wiki... and maybe not. If you would like to get used to the basics of wiki edition, just go to the [sandbox&gt;http://sandbox.xwiki.org]. This space is meant to let you learn by yourself ;-)

There are other steps that you may want to go through, such as :

1. Configuring your wiki by clicking on the 'Administration' link at the top right.
1. Changing the layout and menu contents by using the [Panel Wizard&gt;Panels.PanelWizard?forceLeftPanels=1&amp;forceRightPanels=1]
1. Modifying this page, for example stating what your wiki is all about. Place a couple of carefully phrased sentences on this page. (You just have to click on the Edit button at the top left of the page).
1. Inviting your friends, family or co-workers to enjoy collaboration made easy.
1. Writing your documentation, sharing ideas, creating different spaces and organizing them the way you want.
1. And then write some blog posts in order to summarize your work.

For more information you can visit [the documentation on xwiki.org&gt;http://www.xwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/Main/Documentation].

Let's go! This XWiki is yours, we hope you'll enjoy it ...

Congratulations,
The XWiki Team

